But that is what Water, Sanitation and Human Settlements Minister Lindiwe Sisulu did this week in basking in the thanks of a community to which her department had provided water after years of delay. That, minister, is like thanking the fish for swimming, as someone pointed out on social media. Sisulu has used the Covid-19 crisis, basically, to do her job: delivering water to the people. It is sad that much of that water is still being delivered by tankers because her ANC comrades in local authorities around the country have either deliberately, or negligently, destroyed existing water supply infrastructure....